  "prompt": "My iPhone screen broke I have iCloud, would notifications I received transfer over to a replacement or would contacts transfer and notifications gone?",
  "response": "When you get a replacement iPhone and restore from an iCloud backup, here's what typically happens:\n\n1. Contacts: These will transfer completely when you restore from iCloud backup.\n\n2. Notifications: Historical notifications are usually not preserved. When you restore your iCloud backup to a new device, you'll get recent data like contacts, messages, photos, etc., but past notifications generally do not transfer.\n\nTo ensure a smooth transition:\n- Make sure your iCloud backup is current before getting the replacement\n- When setting up the new iPhone, choose \"Restore from iCloud Backup\" during initial setup\n- Sync all important data like contacts, messages, photos, etc.\n\nTip: Consider taking screenshots of important notifications before getting the replacement if there's critical information you want to keep.",
